|| style=\"background:darkgrey;\" colspan=\"5\"|\n|-\n|style=\"background:lightblue;\"| Marlee\n| IN || IN || IN || style=\"background:crimson;\"|<span style=\"color:white;\">'''QUIT'''</span> || style=\"background:darkgrey;\" colspan=\"5\"|\n|-\n|style=\"background:blue;\"| <span style=\"color:white;\">Christy</span>\n| IN || style=\"background:cornflowerblue;\"|'''WIN''' || style=\"background:tomato;\"|'''OUT''' || style=\"background:darkgrey;\" colspan=\"6\"|\n|-\n|style=\"background:#483d8b;\"| <span style=\"color:white;\">Aleksandra</span>\n| IN || style=\"background:tomato;\"|'''OUT''' || style=\"background:darkgrey;\" colspan=\"7\"|\n|}\n\n: {{Color box|cornflowerblue|border=darkgray}} The contestant was part of the winning team for the episode.\n: {{Color box|orange|border=darkgray}} The contestant was at risk of elimination.\n: {{Color box|tomato|border=darkgray}} The contestant was eliminated from the competition.\n: {{Color box|crimson|border=darkgray}} The contestant withdrew from the competition.\n: {{Color box|lightgreen|border=darkgray}} The contestant was a runner-up.\n: {{Color box|limegreen|border=darkgray}} The contestant won ''The Face''.\n\n:* Episode 1 was the casting episode. The final twelve were divided into individual teams of four as they were selected.\n:* In episode 4, Marlee withdrew from the competition due to personal problems.\n:* In episode 7, both of the remaining models from the losing teams had to face Karolina for elimination. Margaux and Zi Lin were saved, while Stephanie and Jocelyn were eliminated.\n:* In episode 8, Zilin, Devyn, and Margaux were put through to the final runway show while Ebony was eliminated.\n\n=== Campaigns===\n* Episode 1: Natural beauty shots; self-administered 'transformations' with accessories from [[DKNY]] (casting)\n* Episode 2: Grouped in a [[shipyard]] for [[W (magazine)|W Magazine]]\n* Episode 3: Commercial with Cosabella lingerie in teams\n* Episode 4: Kleinfeld bridal dress fashion show\n* Episode 5: Look-books for Marshall's in teams\n* Episode 6: Self-directed commercials for Opensky.com\n* Episode 7: [[Red carpet|Red Carpet]] interviews conducted by [[Wendy Williams]]\n* Episode 8: [[Ulta Beauty|ULTA Beauty]] beauty shots\n\n== Television ratings ==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"width:72%;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" width=7% | No. in<br />series\n! scope=\"col\" width=7% | No. in<br />season\n!  Title\n! scope=\"col\" width=20% | Original air date\n! scope=\"col\" width=14% | U.S. viewers<br/>(million)\n|-\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 1\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 1\n |Title           = The Fight to Make the Final 12\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2013|2|5}}\n |Viewers         = 0.34<ref>{{cite web|title=Tuesday's Cable Ratings: \"Tosh.0\" Returns, \"Hardcore Pawn\" Wraps on Top|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/ratings/2013/02/06/tuesdays-cable-ratings-tosh0-returns-hardcore-pawn-wraps-on-top-287511/cable_20130205/|publisher=The Futon Critic|accessdate=February 14, 2013}}</ref>\n |LineColor       = A780FB\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 2\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 2\n |Title           = Game On!\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2013|2|12}}\n |Viewers         = 0.51<ref>{{cite web|title=Tuesday's Cable Ratings: \"Tosh.0\" Tops Demos, Westminster Dog Show Leads Viewers|url=http://thefutoncritic.com/ratings/2013/02/13/tuesdays-cable-ratings-tosh0-tops-demos-westminster-dog-show-leads-viewers-364410/cable_20130212/|publisher=The Futon Critic|accessdate=February 14, 2013}}</ref>\n |LineColor       = A780FB\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 3\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 3\n |Title           = Model Warfare\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2013|2|19}}\n |Viewers         = 0.46<ref>{{cite web|title=Tuesday's Cable Ratings: \"Tosh.0,\" \"Pretty Little Liars\" Top Demo Race|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/ratings/2013/02/21/tuesdays-cable-ratings-tosh0-pretty-little-liars-top-demo-race-765314/cable_20130219/|publisher=the Futon Critic|a