rst = Elease|title = ABOUT THE SHOW&nbsp;\u2014 Find out all about Oxygen's SO new series The Face!|url = http://the-face.oxygen.com/face/blog/about-the-show|publisher = Oxygen Media|accessdate = October 1, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last = Patten|first = Dominic|title = Oxygen Launches 'The Face' Model Reality Series With Naomi Campbell|url = http://www.deadline.com/2012/05/oxygen-launches-%E2%80%98the-face%E2%80%99-model-reality-series-with-naomi-campbell/|publisher = Deadline Hollywood|accessdate = May 1, 2012|url-status = dead|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20120505175544/http://www.deadline.com/2012/05/oxygen-launches-%e2%80%98the-face%e2%80%99-model-reality-series-with-naomi-campbell/|archivedate = May 5, 2012|df = mdy-all}}</ref> The premiere season followed three supermodel coaches as they competed with each other to find 'the face' of cosmetic retail giant [[Ulta Beauty]].\n\nSupermodel and executive produce [[Naomi Campbell]], together with supermodels [[Karol\u00edna Kurkov\u00e1|Karolina Kurkova]] and [[Coco Rocha]], served as supermodel mentors for the first season. [[Nigel Barker (photographer)|Nigel Barker]], a previous judge for cycles 2 to 18 of ''[[America's Next Top Model]]'', serve as host as well. It featured 12 aspiring contestants from the United States of America, Canada, China, Belarus, and Australia.\n\nThe winner of the competition was 21-year-old Devyn Abdullah from [[The Bronx|Bronx, New York]].\n\n== Casting process ==\nAspiring contestants for the show had to pre-register themselves online, and were encouraged to attend open casting calls or send in a video and application. The deadline for all applications was August 3, 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/ratings/2013/02/06/tuesdays-cable-ratings-tosh0-returns-hardcore-pawn-wraps-on-top-287511/cable_20130205/ |title=Tuesday's Cable Ratings: \"Tosh.0\" Returns, \"Hardcore Pawn\" Wraps on Top |website=The Futon Critic |access-date=February 14, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://thefutoncritic.com/ratings/2013/02/13/tuesdays-cable-ratings-tosh0-tops-demos-westminster-dog-show-leads-viewers-364410/cable_20130212/ |title=Tuesday's Cable Ratings: \"Tosh.0\" Tops Demos, Westminster Dog Show Leads Viewers |website=The Futon Critic |access-date=February 14, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/ratings/2013/02/21/tuesdays-cable-ratings-tosh0-pretty-little-liars-top-demo-race-765314/cable_20130219/ |title=Tuesday's Cable Ratings: \"Tosh.0,\" \"Pretty Little Liars\" Top Demo Race |website=The Futon Critic |access-date=February 22, 2013}}</ref> The show required all contestants to be 18 years old and over at the time of auditioning in order to be eligible for the program. Contestants from any country around the world could apply, as long as they had all the required documentation in order to remain in the United States for the duration of the series.<ref>{{cite web|title = Participant Application|url = http://www.thefacecasting.com/uploads/files/thefaceapplication.pdf}}</ref>\n\n== Contestants ==\n(''Ages stated are at start of filming'')\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center; \n! Contestant\n! Age\n! Height\n! Hometown\n! Model coach\n! Finish\n! Rank\n|-\n| Aleksandra Dubrovskaya\n| 24\n| {{height|m=1.77}}\n| [[Murmansk]], [[Russia]]\n| '''<span style=\"color:#483d8b\">Naomi</span>'''\n| Episode 2\n| 12 \n|-\n| Christy Nelson\n| 25\n| {{height|m=1.81}}\n| [[Atascadero, California|Atascadero]]\n| '''<span style=\"color:blue\">Karolina</span>'''\n| Episode 3\n| 11\n|-\n| Marlee Nichols\n| 22\n| {{height|m=1.75}}\n| [[Los Angeles]]\n| '''<span style=\"color:royalblue\">Coco</span>'''\n|rowspan=\"2\"| Episode 4\n| 10 (quit) \n|-\n| [[Brittany Mason]]\n| 27\n| {{height|m=1.78}}\n| [[Anderson, Indiana|Anderson]]\n|  '''<span style=\"color:royalblue\">Coco</span>'''\n| 9\n|-\n| Madeleine Armstrong\n| 24\n| {{height|m=1.75}}\n| [[Melbourne]], [[Australia]]\n| '''<span style=\"color:blue\">Karolina</span>'''\n| Episode 5\n| 8\n|-\n| Sandra Woodley\n| 22\n| {{height|m=1.78}}\n| [[Philadelphia]]\n| '''<span style=\"color:#483d8b\">Naomi</span>'''\n| Episode 6\n| 7\n|-\n| Stephanie Lalanne\n| 22\n| {{height|m=1.78}}\n| [[San Francisco]]\n| '''<span style=\"color:royalblue\">Coco</span>'''\n|rowspan=\"2\"| Episode 7\n|rowspan=\"2\"| 6-5\n|-\n| Jocelyn Chew\n| 21\n| {{height|m=1.75}}\n| [[Victoria, British Columbia|Victoria]], [[Canada]]\n|  '''<span style=\"color:#483d8b\">Naomi</span>'''\n|-\n| Ebony Olivia Grace Smith\n| 22\n| {{height|m=1.75}}\n| [[Indianapolis]]\n| '''<span style=\"color:blue\">Karolina</span>'''\n|rowspan=\"4\"| Episode 8\n| 4\n|-\n| Margaux Brooke Snell\n| 22\n| {{height|m=1.70}}\n| [[Roswell, Georgia|Roswell]]\n| '''<span style=\"color:royalblue\">Coco</span>'''\n|rowspan=\"2\"| 3-2\n|-\n| [[Luo Zilin]]\n| 26\n| {{height|m=1.83}}\n| [[Zhejiang]], [[China]]\n| '''<span style=\"color:#483d8b\">Naomi</span>'''\n|-\n| Devyn Abdullah\n| 22\n| {{height|m=1.80}}\n| [[The Bronx]]\n| '''<span style=\"color:blue\">Karolina</span>'''\n| 1\n|}\n{{clear}}\n[[File:TFSeason 1cast.jpg|thumb|300px|Contestants]]\n\n== Episodes==\n\n=== Episode 1: The Fight to Make the Final 12 ===\n''First aired February 5, 2013''\n\nSupermodels [[Coco Rocha]], [[Karolina Kurkova]], and [[Naomi Campbell]] begin their search for 'The Face'. The final three teams are selected, and the hopefuls move one step closer to the ultimate prize.\n\n=== Episode 2: Game On! ===\n''First aired February 12, 2013''\n\nThe final twelve move into their new loft in [[New York City]], and they are coached through their very first campaign photo shoot by their supermodel mentors. The goal is to create an ad campaign worthy of being featured on the pages of ''[[W (magazine)|W Magazine]]''.\n\n* '''Winning coach and team:'''  '''<span style=\"color:blue\">Karolina Kurkova</span>'''\n* '''Bottom two:''' <span style=\"color:#483d8b\">Aleksandra Dubrovskaya</span> & <span style=\"color:royalblue\">Stephanie Lalanne</span>\n* '''Eliminated:''' <span style=\"color:#483d8b\">Aleksandra Dubrovskaya</span>\n* '''Featured Photographer:''' [[Patrick Demarchelier]]\n* '''Special Guests:''' [[Bethann Hardison]], Claudine Ingeneri, [[Stefano Tonchi]]\n\n=== Episode 3: Model Warfare ===\n''First aired February 19, 2013''\n\nThe remaining contestants undergo a challenge for Vogue Eyewear, and pressure mounts as bickering begins to ravage Team Naomi. For the shoot, the models must perform a commercial in Cosabella [[lingerie]] with their teammates.\n\n* '''Winning coach and team:'''  '''<span style=\"color:#483d8b\">Naomi Campbell</span>'''\n* '''Bottom two:''' <span style=\"color:blue\">Christy Nelson</span> & <span style=\"color:royalblue\">Stephanie Lalanne</span>\n* '''Eliminated:''' <span style=\"color:blue\">Christy Nelson</span>\n* '''Featured Videographer:''' [[Brendan O'Carroll]]\n* '''Special Guests:''' Guido Campello\n\n=== Episode 4: Falling From Grace ===\n''First aired February 26, 2013''\n\nAn unexpected turn of events sees one girl leaving the competition for good. The girls take part in their first runway show for Kleinfeld Bridal, and they must walk in couture bridal gowns on a grand staircase. After the winning team is revealed, it's goodbye for another one of the wannabe models.\n\n* '''Quit:''' <span style=\"color:royalblue\">Marlee Nichols</span>\n* '''Winning coach and team:'''  '''<span style=\"color:#483d8b\">Naomi Campbell</span>\n* '''Bottom two:''' <span style=\"color:royalblue\">Brittany Mason</span> & <span style=\"color:blue\">Ebony Olivia Smith</span>\n* '''Eliminated:''' <span style=\"color:royalblue\">Brittany Mason</span>\n\n=== Episode 5: We Are the Most Miserable Team Here ===\n''First aired March 5, 2013''\n\nThe eight remaining models prepare for a dancing challenge, and must later shoot for a Marshall's lookbook with their teammates. The arguments between Jocelyn and Sandra reach an all-time high when Naomi steps in to intervene, and a shocking elimination catches one team by surprise.\n\n* '''Winning coach and team:'''  '''<span style=\"color:#483d8b\">Naomi Campbell</span>'''\n* '''Bottom two:''' <span style=\"color:blue\">Madeline Armstrong</span> & <span style=\"color:royalblue\">Stephanie Lalanne</span>\n* '''Eliminated:''' <span style=\"color:blue\">Madeline Armstrong</span>\n\n=== Episode 6: Every Rose Has its Thorns ===\n''First aired March 12, 2013''\n\nThe hopefuls prepare for their latest test shoot challenge \u2014 shooting a commercial for [[Christian Louboutin]] shoes. Tempers flare when one model threatens to leave the competition. For the campaign, the teams must write their own scripts and direct a commercial in which they attempt to sell miscellaneous items from Opensky.com.\n\n* '''Winning coach and team:'''  '''<span style=\"color:blue\">Karolina Kurkova</span>'''\n* '''Bottom two:''' <span style=\"color:royalblue\">Margaux Brooke Snell</span> &  <span style=\"color:#483d8b\">Sandra Woodley</span>\n* '''Eliminated:''' <span style=\"color:#483d8b\">Sandra Woodley</span>\n\n=== Episode 7: Red Carpet Ready? ===\n''First aired March 19, 2013''\n\nThe girls learn about the double elimination that will be taking place, and prepare to win the final campaign that will assure them a place in the finale. After the glitz and glamour of the [[red carpet]] and a surprise interview conducted by [[Wendy Williams]], the winning coach must decide which two girls will be sent home. Model [[Pat Cleveland]] makes an appearance to prepare the girls for the competition.\n\n* '''Winning coach and team:'''  '''<span style=\"color:blue\">Karolina Kurkova</span>'''\n* '''Bottom four:''' <span style=\"color:#483d8b\">Jocelyn Chew</span>, <span style=\"color:royalblue\">Margaux Brooke Snell</span>, <span style=\"color:royalblue\">Stephanie Lalanne</span> & <span style=\"color:#483d8b\">Luo Zilin</span>\n* '''Eliminated:''' <span style=\"color:#483d8b\">Jocelyn Chew</span> & <span style=\"color:royalblue\">Stephanie Lalanne</span>\n\n=== Episode 8: Finding the Face... The Finale ===\n''First aired March 26, 2013''\n\nThe remaining four contestants take part in their final shoot for ULTA beauty. One last surprise elimination sees only three of the models put through to the final task, which is walking in the runway for a [[Zac Posen]] fashion show.\n\n* '''Final four:''' <span style=\"color:blue\">Devyn Abdullah</span>, <span style=\"color:blue\">Ebony Olivia Smith</span>, <span style=\"color:royalblue\">Margaux Brooke Snell</span> & <span style=\"color:#483d8b\">Luo Zilin</span>\n* '''Eliminated:''' <span style=\"color:blue\">Ebony Olivia Smith</span>\n* '''Final three:''' <span style=\"color:blue\">Devyn Abdullah</span>, <span style=\"color:royalblue\">Margaux Brooke Snell</span> & <span style=\"color:#483d8b\">Luo Zilin</span>\n* '''The Face of ULTA Beauty:''' <span style=\"color:blue\">Devyn Abdullah</span>\n* '''Winning coach and team:'''  '''<span style=\"color:blue\">Karolina Kurkova</span>\n\n== Summaries ==\n\n=== Elimination table===\n\n{| style=\"text-align: center; font-size:90%; line-height:20px;\" class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n|width=\"265\" style=\"background:lightblue;\"|Team Coco||width=\"265\" style=\"background:blue;\"|<span style=\"color:white;\">Team Karolina</span>||width=\"265\" style=\"background:#483d8b;\"|<span style=\"color:white;\">Team Naomi</span>\n|}\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; font-size:100%\"\n|-\n! rowspan=2 | Contestant\n! colspan=9 | Episodes\n|-\n! style=\"width:60px;\"| 1 \n! style=\"width:60px;\"| 2 \n! style=\"width:60px;\"| 3 \n! style=\"width:60px;\"| 4 \n! style=\"width:60px;\"| 5\n! style=\"width:60px;\"| 6\n! style=\"width:60px;\"| 7 \n! colspan=\"2\"| 8\n|-\n| {{nowrap|'''''Challenge Winner'''''}}\n| {{N/A}}\n| ''Zilin''\n| ''Madeleine''\n| ''Margaux''\n| ''Ebony''\n| ''Stephanie''\n| ''Zilin''\n| colspan=2 {{N/A}}\n|-\n|style=\"background:blue;\"| <span style=\"color:white;\">Devyn</span>\n| IN || style=\"background:cornflowerblue;\"|'''WIN''' || IN || IN || IN || style=\"background:cornflowerblue;\"|'''WIN''' || style=\"background:cornflowerblue;\"|'''WIN''' || IN || style=\"background:limegreen;\"|'''WINNER'''\n|-\n|style=\"background:#483d8b;\"| <span style=\"color:white;\">Zilin</span>\n| IN || IN || style=\"background:cornflowerblue;\"|'''WIN''' || style=\"background:cornflowerblue;\"|'''WIN''' || style=\"background:cornflowerblue;\"|'''WIN''' || IN || style=\"background:orange;\"|'''LOW''' || IN || width=\"60\" style=\"background:lightgreen;\"|'''{{nowrap|RUNNER-UP }}'''\n|-\n|style=\"background:lightblue;\"| Margaux\n| IN || IN || IN || IN || IN || style=\"background:orange;\"|'''LOW''' || style=\"background:orange;\"|'''LOW''' || IN || width=\"60\" style=\"background:lightgreen;\"|'''{{nowrap|RUNNER-UP }}'''\n|-\n|style=\"background:blue;\"| <span style=\"color:white;\">Ebony</span>\n| IN || style=\"background:cornflowerblue;\"|'''WIN''' || IN || style=\"background:orange;\"|'''LOW''' || IN || style=\"background:cornflowerblue;\"|'''WIN''' || style=\"background:cornflowerblue;\"|'''WIN''' || width=\"60\" style=\"background:tomato;\"|'''OUT''' || style=\"background:darkgrey;\" colspan=\"1\"|\n|-\n|style=\"background:#483d8b;\"| <span style=\"color:white;\">Jocelyn</span>\n| IN || IN || style=\"background:cornflowerblue;\"|'''WIN''' || style=\"background:cornflowerblue;\"|'''WIN''' || style=\"background:cornflowerblue;\"|'''WIN''' || IN || style=\"background:tomato;\"|'''OUT''' || style=\"background:darkgrey;\" colspan=\"2\"|\n|-\n|style=\"background:lightblue;\"| Stephanie\n| IN || style=\"background:orange;\"|'''LOW''' || style=\"background:orange;\"|'''LOW''' || IN || style=\"background:orange;\"|'''LOW''' || IN || style=\"background:tomato;\"|'''OUT''' || style=\"background:darkgrey;\" colspan=\"2\"|\n|-\n|style=\"background:#483d8b;\"| <span style=\"color:white;\">Sandra</span>\n| IN || IN || style=\"background:cornflowerblue;\"|