blic of Iran Football Federation|Iran]])\n*Fourth official: [[Francisco Oscar Lamolina]] ([[Asociaci\u00f3n del F\u00fatbol Argentino|Argentina]])\n<includeonly>|}</includeonly><section end=Lineups />\n| width=50% valign=top|\n'''Match Rules'''\n*90 minutes.\n*30 minutes of [[extra time]] if necessary.\n*Penalty shoot-out if scores still level.\n*Two [[substitute (football)|substitutions]] permitted, plus one for the goalkeeper.\n|}\n\n==Post-match==\n[[Vice President of the United States|U.S. Vice President]] [[Al Gore]], [[List of Presidents of UEFA|UEFA president]] [[Lennart Johansson]], and [[List of presidents of FIFA|FIFA president]] [[Jo\u00e3o Havelange]] were among those present at the stands during the awards ceremony. Vice President Gore handed the trophy to Brazilian captain [[Dunga]].<ref name=\"coming\"/><ref>{{YouTube |pLPM_JSbGvI|Brazil v Italy - The Final - 1994 FIFA World Cup USA\u2122}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Brazil\u2013Italy football rivalry]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{1994 FIFA World Cup}}\n{{FIFA World Cup}}\n{{Brazil national football team matches}}\n{{Italy national football team matches}}\n{{Portal bar|Association football|Greater Los Angeles|1990s|Brazil|Italy}}\n\n[[Category:FIFA World Cup finals|1994]]\n[[Category:Brazil national football team matches|1994]]\n[[Category:Italy national football team matches|1994]]\n[[Category:1994 FIFA World Cup|1]]\n[[Category:Brazil at the 1994 FIFA World Cup|Final]]\n[[Category:Association football penalty shoot-outs|Fifa World Cup Final 1994]]\n[[Category:Brazil\u2013Italy relations]]\n[[Category:Italy at the 1994 FIFA World Cup|Final]]\n[[Category:Sports competitions in Pasadena, California]]\n[[Category:International sports competitions in California]]\n[[Category:1994 in sports in California]]\n[[Category:20th century in Pasadena, California]]\n[[Category:July 1994 sports events in the United States|FIFA World Cup final]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use American English|date=July 2019}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=May 2019}}\n{{Infobox football match\n|              title = 1994 FIFA World Cup Final\n| image = 2018.06.17 Over the Rose Bowl, Pasadena, CA USA 0040 (42855674681).jpg\n| image_size = \n|            caption = [[Rose Bowl (stadium)|Rose Bowl stadium]], the Final venue, photographed in 2018.\n|              event = [[1994 FIFA World Cup]]\n|              team1 = [[Brazil national football team|Brazil]]\n|   team1association = {{flagdeco|BRA|size=30px}}\n|         team1score = 0\n|              team2 = [[Italy national football team|Italy]]\n|   team2association = {{flagdeco|ITA|size=30px}}\n|         team2score = 0\n|            details = After [[Overtime (sports)#Association football|extra time]] <br> Brazil won 3\u20132 on [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|penalties]]\n|               date = July 17, 1994\n|            stadium = [[Rose Bowl (stadium)|Rose Bowl]]\n|               city = [[Pasadena, California|Pasadena]], [[California]]\n| man_of_the_match1a =\n|            referee = [[S\u00e1ndor Puhl]] ([[Hungarian Football Federation|Hungary]])\n|         attendance = 94,194\n|            weather = Scattered clouds<br />{{convert|38|\u00b0C|\u00b0F|order=flip}}<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.eurosport.com/football/world-cup/2014/factbox-dates-and-weather-at-previous-world-cups_sto3945963/story.shtml | title=FACTBOX-Dates and weather at previous World Cups | date=July 17, 1994 | publisher=Eurosport | accessdate=June 29, 2019 }}</ref>\n|           previous = [[1990 FIFA World Cup Final|1990]]\n|               next = [[1998 FIFA World Cup Final|1998]]\n}}\nThe '''1994 FIFA World Cup Final''' was a [[association football|soccer]] game that took place at the [[Rose Bowl (stadium)|Rose Bowl]] in [[Pasadena, California|Pasadena]], [[California]], United States, on July 17, 1994 to determine the winner of the [[1994 FIFA World Cup]]. [[Brazil national football team|Brazil]] beat [[Italy national football team|Italy]] 3\u20132 on [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|penalties]] to claim their fourth World Cup title when the match finished 0\u20130 after [[Overtime (sports)#Association football|extra time]]; this meant that Brazil surpassed Italy and Germany as the tournament's most successful nation.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.planetworldcup.com/CUPS/1994/final_bra_v_ita.html|title=1994 FIFA World Cup Final Details |date= |work=Planet World Cup |accessdate=October 11, 2012 }}</ref>\n\nIt was the first World Cup final to be both scoreless in regular and extra time and to be decided by a penalty shoot-out. [[FIFA World Cup awards#Golden Ball|Silver Ball]] winner [[Roberto Baggio]] missed the decisive penalty for Italy.<ref name=\"FIFA 94\">[https://www.fifa.com/classicfootball/players/player=174363/ \"Divine by moniker, divine by magic\"]. FIFA.com. Retrieved June 1, 2014</ref> Brazil had previously beaten Italy in the [[1970 FIFA World Cup Final|1970 final]], marking the 1994 final as the second time that the same teams had met in two different World Cup finals, after [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]] and [[Germany national football team|Germany]] met in [[1986 FIFA World Cup Final|1986]] and [[1990 FIFA World Cup Final|1990]].<ref>{{cite web |title=The Story of the 1994 World Cup |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/blogs/chrisbevan/2010/05/the_story_of_the_1994_world_cu.html |work=BBC Sport |date= |accessdate=October 11, 2012 }}</ref><ref name=\"coming\">{{cite news |first=John F. |last=Molinaro |title=1994 World Cup: Coming to America |url=http://www.cbc.ca/sports/soccer/1994-world-cup-coming-to-america-1.779022 |publisher=CBC Sports (CBC/Radio-Canada) |date=November 21, 2009 |accessdate=February 26, 2015 }}</ref> Played at 12:30 local time, this was the most recent World Cup final to be played in a broad daylight.\n\nFIFA awarded the final game of the tournament to the famous college sports stadium near [[Los Angeles]] on June 30, 1992; the Rose Bowl was the largest stadium used for the tournament.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://articles.latimes.com/1992-06-30/sports/sp-1347_1_world-cup-ticket | title=Rose Bowl Gets Final of World Cup | date=June 30, 1992 | first=Rone | last=Tempest | newspaper=Los Angeles Times | accessdate=March 8, 2019 }}</ref> \n\nThe Brazilian team dedicated their win to the late triple [[Formula One]] [[motor racing]] [[List of Formula One World Drivers' Champions|world champion]] [[Ayrton Senna]], who had [[Death of Ayrton Senna|died]] in an accident at that year's [[1994 San Marino Grand Prix|San Marino Grand Prix]] in Italy two and a half months before.<ref>{{cite news |first=Alex |last=Bellos |title=Brazil still in thrall to the Senna legend |url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2004/apr/22/formulaone.comment |work=The Guardian |publisher=Guardian News and Media |date=April 22, 2004 |accessdate=February 26, 2015 }}</ref> With Italy finishing as runners-up, [[Franco Baresi]] became the sixth player in history to win gold, silver and bronze medals at the FIFA World Cup.<ref>[https://www.fifa.com/classicfootball/players/player=174375/ Milan and Italy's imperial sweeper. Franco BARESI]</ref><ref>Previously this result was attained in 1974 by five German players: Sepp Maier, Franz Beckenbauer, Wolfgang Overath, J\u00fcrgen Grabowski and Horst-Dieter H\u00f6ttges.</ref>\n\n==Route to the final==\n{| style=\"width:100%;text-align:center\"\n|- style=\"vertical-align:top;background:#9cf\"\n!colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:1*\"|Brazil\n!Round\n!colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:1*\"|Italy\n|- style=\"vertical-align:top;background:#c1e0ff\"\n|Opponent\n|Result\n||[[1994 FIFA World Cup#Group stage|Group stage]]\n|Opponent\n|Result\n|-\n|{{fb|RUS}}\n|[[1994 FIFA World Cup Group B#Brazil vs Russia|2\u20130]]\n| style=\"background:#c1e0ff\"|Match 1\n|{{fb|IRL}}\n|[[1994 FIFA World Cup Group E#Italy vs Republic of Ireland|0\u20131]]\n|-\n|{{fb|CMR}}\n|[[1994 FIFA World Cup Group B#Brazil vs Cameroon|3\u20130]]\n| style=\"background:#c1e0ff\"|Match 2\n|{{fb|NOR}}\n|[[1994 FIFA World Cup Group E#Italy vs Norway|1\u20130]]\n|-\n|{{fb|SWE}}\n|[[1994 FIFA World Cup Group B#Brazil vs Sweden|1\u20131]]\n| style=\"background:#c1e0ff\"|Match 3\n|{{fb|MEX}}\n|[[1994 FIFA World Cup Group E#Italy vs Mexico|1\u20131]]\n|-\n|colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\"|\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|-\n!width=\"175\"|Team\n!width=\"20\"|{{Tooltip| Pld | Played}}\n!width=\"20\"|{{Tooltip| W | Won}}\n!width=\"20\"|{{Tooltip| D | Drawn}}\n!width=\"20\"|{{Tooltip| L | Lost}}\n!width=\"20\"|{{Tooltip| GF | Goals for}}\n!width=\"20\"|{{Tooltip| GA | Goals against}}\n!width=\"20\"|{{Tooltip| GD | Goal difference}}\n!width=\"20\"|{{Tooltip| Pts | Points}}\n|- style=\"background:#cfc\"\n|align=left|'''{{fb|BRA}}'''\n|3||2||1||0||6||1||+5||'''7'''\n|- style=\"background:#cfc\"\n|align=left|{{fb|SWE}}\n|3||1||2||0||6||4||+2||'''5'''\n|-\n|align=left|{{fb|RUS}}\n|3||1||0||2||7||6||+1||'''3'''\n|-\n|align=left|{{fb|CMR}}\n|3||0||1||2||3||11||\u22128||'''1'''\n|}\n|style=\"background:#c1e0ff\"|Final standing\n|colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\"|\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|-\n!width=\"175\"|Team\n!width=\"20\"|{{Tooltip| Pld | Played}}\n!width=\"20\"|{{Tooltip| W | Won}}\n!width=\"20\"|{{Tooltip| D | Drawn}}\n!width=\"20\"|{{Tooltip| L | Lost}}\n!width=\"20\"|{{Tooltip| GF | Goals for}}\n!width=\"20\"|{{Tooltip| GA | Goals against}}\n!width=\"20\"|{{Tooltip| GD | Goal difference}}\n!width=\"20\"|{{Tooltip| Pts | Points}}\n|- style=\"background:#cfc\"\n|align=left|{{fb|MEX}}\n|3||1||1||1||3||3||0||'''4'''\n|- style=\"background:#cfc\"\n|align=left|{{fb|IRL}}\n|3||1||1||1||2||2||0||'''4'''\n|- style=\"background:#cfc\"\n|align=left|'''{{fb|ITA}}'''\n|3||1||1||1||2||2||0||'''4'''\n|-\n|align=left|{{fb|NOR}}\n|3||1||1||1||1||1||0||'''4'''\n|}\n|- style=\"vertical-align:top;background:#c1e0ff\"\n|Opponent\n|Result\n||[[1994 FIFA World Cup knockout stage|Knockout stage]]\n|Opponent\n|Result\n|-\n|{{fb|USA}}\n|[[1994 FIFA World Cup knockout stage#Brazil vs United States|1\u20130]]\n| style=\"background:#c1e0ff\"|Round of 16\n|{{fb|NGA}}\n|[[1994 FIFA World Cup knockout stage#Nigeria vs Italy|2\u20131]] ([[Overtime (sports)#Association football|aet]])\n|-\n|{{fb|NED}}\n|[[1994 FIFA World Cup knockout stage#Netherlands vs Brazil|3\u20132]]\n| style=\"background:#c1e0ff\"|Quarter-finals\n|{{fb|ESP}}\n|[[1994 FIFA World Cup knockout stage#Italy vs Spain|2\u20131]]\n|-\n|{{fb|SWE}}\n|[[1994 FIFA World Cup knockout stage#Sweden vs Brazil|1\u20130]]\n| style=\"background:#c1e0ff\"|Semi-finals\n|{{fb|BUL}}\n|[[1994 FIFA World Cup knockout stage#Bulgaria vs Italy|2\u20131]]\n|}\n\n==Match==\n\n===Summary===\nIn what was, and still is as of 2018, the only World Cup Final not to have a goal scored, the game would come to be defined by missed opportunities. Chances were few and far between in the first half, as [[Rom\u00e1rio]] had Brazil's best chance of the half with a header, but he headed straight at [[Gianluca Pagliuca]]. Late in the first half, [[Daniele Massaro]] had what would turn out to be Italy's best chance of the match, as he had a good opportunity from the edge of the box after a counter-attack, but his shot was saved by [[Cl\u00e1udio Taffarel]]. The second half was largely devoid of scoring chances, as Brazil were unable to break through the center back pairing of [[Franco Baresi]] and [[Paolo Maldini]]. The lack of attacking play in the match was down to strong holding midfield play by [[Dino Baggio]] for Italy, and by both [[Dunga]] and [[Mauro Silva]] for Brazil.<ref name=\"fifa.com\">https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/archive/usa1994/index.html</ref>\n\nAs extra time began, chances would become more plentiful, as Brazil began to dominate play. Rom\u00e1rio had another chance early in extra time after Pagliuca made an ill advised decision to come for a cross, leaving the goal exposed, but [[Bebeto]] was unable to find him. [[Roberto Baggio]], who had been quiet for most of the match having picked up an injury earlier in the tournament, had his only sight of goal in the entire match in the first half of extra time, hitting a shot from around 25 yards, but Taffarel pushed the shot over. [[Zinho]] had a chance on the stroke of halftime in extra time, hitting his shot well from inside the area, but Pagliuca saved well at his near post. In the second half of extra time, Rom\u00e1rio missed a golden chance to hand Brazil the trophy, as [[Cafu]] had found him inside the six yard box. With Pagliuca at least four yards away from him on the other side of the goal, and the entire goal to aim at, the off balance Rom\u00e1rio put his shot wide of the post.<ref name=\"fifa.com\"/>\n\nThis was the first time the World Cup would be decided on penalties. Italian captain Baresi took the first penalty and blazed his penalty over the bar. Brazilian center back [[M\u00e1rcio Roberto dos Santos|Marcio Santos]] went next, but Pagliuca saved the Brazilian  defender's effort low to his right. [[Demetrio Albertini]] went next for Italy, scoring his penalty into the top corner. Rom\u00e1rio was next for Brazil, and he scored his penalty, placing it so far in the corner that it went in off the post, tying the score at 1\u20131. [[Alberigo Evani]] went third for Italy, he scored, putting his penalty high and in the middle, as Taffarel dove to the right. [[Branco (footballer)|Branco]] went next for Brazil, and he scored in the bottom left corner. Massaro, who had scored twice in the Champions League Final less than two months previously, went next for Italy, but he was unable to put the ball in Taffarel's net just as he had been unable to do in the match, as the Brazilian keeper saved to his left. Brazilian captain Dunga was next, and he comfortably placed his shot into the bottom left corner, making it match point. With Italy needing to score to keep their dreams alive, talisman Baggio stepped up to take the penalty. In what would become an infamous moment in World Cup History, Baggio blazed his penalty over the bar, in similar fashion to Baresi, and this gave Brazil their fourth title.<ref name=\"fifa.com\"/><ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dWI6Y9V5fvI</ref>\n\n===Details===\n<section begin=Final />{{Football box\n|date = July 17, 1994\n|time = 12:30 [[Pacific Time Zone|PDT]]\n|team1 = {{fb-rt|BRA}}\n|score = 0\u20130\n|aet = yes\n|report = https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/matches/round=3459/match=3104/index.html\n|team2 = {{fb|ITA}}\n|stadium = [[Rose Bowl (stadium)|Rose Bowl]], [[Pasadena, California|Pasadena]]\n|attendance = 94,194\n|referee = [[S\u00e1ndor Puhl]] ([[Hungarian Football Federation|Hungary]])\n|penalties1 = [[M\u00e1rcio Roberto dos Santos|M\u00e1rcio Santos]] {{penmiss}}<br />[[Rom\u00e1rio]] {{pengoal}}<br />[[Branco (footballer)|Branco]] {{pengoal}}<br />[[Dunga]] {{pengoal}}\n|penaltyscore = 3\u20132\n|penalties2 = {{penmiss}} [[Franco Baresi|Baresi]]<br />{{pengoal}} [[Demetrio Albertini|Albertini]]<br />{{pengoal}} [[Alberigo Evani|Evani]]<br />{{penmiss}} [[Daniele Massaro|Massaro]]<br />{{penmiss}} [[Roberto Baggio|R. Baggio]]\n}}<section end=Final />\n<section begin=Lineups />\n{| width=92%\n|-\n|{{Football kit\n | pattern_la = _brazil1994\n | pattern_b  = _brazil1994WC\n | pattern_ra = _brazil1994\n | pattern_so = _brazil1994\n | leftarm    = FFFF00\n | body       = FFFF00\n | rightarm   = FFFF00\n | shorts     = 0000FF\n | socks      = FFFFFF\n | title      = Brazil\n}}\n|{{Football kit\n | pattern_la = _italia_cm1994\n | pattern_b  = _italia_cm1994_b\n | pattern_ra = _italia_cm1994\n | pattern_so = _italia_cm1994\n | leftarm    = 1004CE\n | body       = 1004CE\n | rightarm   = 1004CE\n | shorts     = FFFFFF\n | socks      = 1004CE\n | title      = Italy\n}}\n|}\n\n{| width=\"100%\"\n|valign=\"top\" width=\"40%\"|\n{| style=\"font-size:90%\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\"\n|-\n!width=25| !!width=25|\n|-\n|GK ||'''1''' ||[[Cl\u00e1udio Taffarel]]\n|-\n|RB ||'''2''' ||